Well as been said a million times for the last ten pages, Maynard's style of writing lyrics is so cryptic yet universal that almost every song will have a different meaning to everyone, & even those meanings that make the most  common sense still have nothing to do with what Maynard may have actually meant.
My interpretation is failry close with most of those already printed but I will try & sum it up verse by verse. 
To me it is indeed about coping with a troubled childhood while still struggling to be a loving parent & not repeating the past...breaking the cycle if you will.
He starts off the song by talking about watching his son be born. "What's coming through is alive & whats holding up is a mirror" (referring to when the doctors hold the child up to the new parents for a first look.)Then he starts to referring to watching his son grow up 'Whats singing songs is a snake" (the demons he wrestles with) "looking to turn my piss to wine" (offering an easy way of coping with difficult situations which occur often during this stage of infancy/toddlerhood) "Theyre both totally void of hate yet killing me just the same" (As much as he loves his child & the childs mother, he sometimes feel that need to lash out at them in whatever manner & its a constant battle between good & evil.)

